      "summary": "A Google-shaped `findOrCreateUser` overload remains after production callers moved to `NormalizedIdentity`.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "incomplete_migration",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/UserService.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/model/AuthFlow.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/controller/AuthController.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/OAuth2SuccessHandler.java"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`AuthController` and `OAuth2SuccessHandler` both call `userService.findOrCreateUser(identity)` with a `NormalizedIdentity`, which is the provider-neutral production path.",
          "`UserService` still keeps `findOrCreateUser(String googleId, String email, String name, String pictureUrl, String loginMethod)`, and that method does nothing except adapt into `NormalizedIdentity.google(...)`.",
          "`AuthFlow.fromLoginMethod(...)` is only used by that legacy overload, which means the old string-based path survives mainly to support the older API shape rather than an active production need."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Remove the Google-specific string overload and route any remaining callers directly through `NormalizedIdentity` plus explicit `AuthFlow`, then delete `AuthFlow.fromLoginMethod(...)` if no real production boundary still needs to parse the old field.",
