    {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::incomplete_migration::legacy_google_id_column_repurposed_for_all_providers",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "summary": "The legacy `google_id` compatibility column is still populated for non-Google identities.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "incomplete_migration",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/UserService.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/model/User.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/repository/UserRepository.java",
          "docs/specs/2026-03-13-microsoft-sso-design.md"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`UserService.createNewUser(...)` and `applyProviderIdentityFields(...)` always write `user.setGoogleId(legacyGoogleCompatibilityId(identity))`.",
          "For non-Google identities, `legacyGoogleCompatibilityId(...)` synthesizes values like `microsoft:<providerUserId>`, so the legacy column is being used as a generic compatibility bucket instead of a Google-only bridge.",
          "Reads are already provider-aware first via `findByProviderAndProviderUserId(...)`, and the fallback `findByGoogleId(...)` is only consulted when `identity.provider() == AuthProvider.GOOGLE`, so non-Google synthetic `google_id` values are not part of the active lookup path.",
          "The migration spec tracks dual-writing `google_id` for Google compatibility and later retirement of the column, but it does not describe storing non-Google synthetic identities in that legacy field."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Confine `google_id` writes to the actual Google-compatibility path only, stop populating synthetic non-Google values into that column, and leave the legacy field as a narrow Google bridge until the planned cleanup release removes it.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "0091cada"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "kind": "issue",
      "primary_command": "desloppify plan resolve \"review::.::holistic::incomplete_migration::legacy_google_id_column_repurposed_for_all_providers\" --note \"<what you did>\" --confirm",
