    {
      "id": "review::.::holistic::incomplete_migration::login_method_and_last_login_flow_overlap",
      "confidence": "high",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "summary": "Old `loginMethod` and new `lastLoginFlow` contracts still coexist for the same concept.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "incomplete_migration",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/UserService.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/model/User.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/controller/dto/UserResponse.java",
          "frontend/src/hooks/useAuth.ts",
          "frontend/src/pages/DashboardPage.tsx",
          "docs/plans/2026-03-13-microsoft-sso-implementation.md"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`UserService.applyProviderIdentityFields(...)` sets both `user.setLastLoginFlow(identity.loginFlow())` and `user.setLoginMethod(identity.loginFlow().name())`, so the old and new fields are populated from the same source.",
          "`UserResponse.from(...)` exposes both `loginMethod` and `lastLoginFlow` even though they describe the same flow/channel value.",
          "`useAuth` types only `loginMethod`, and `DashboardPage` renders only that field, so the frontend still follows the older contract while the backend also publishes the newer `lastLoginFlow` field.",
          "The Microsoft implementation plan explicitly calls out returning `provider`, `providerUserId`, and `lastLoginFlow` from `/api/user/me`, but it does not establish `loginMethod` as part of the new provider-aware surface."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Collapse the public/current-user flow contract onto `lastLoginFlow` (or one clearly named successor), update the frontend to consume that field, and keep `loginMethod` only at a temporary serialization boundary if an external consumer still needs it; otherwise remove the duplicate field and its parser entirely.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "5da14a09"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "kind": "issue",
