      "id": "review::.::holistic::error_consistency::legacy_login_flow_uses_null_sentinel",
      "confidence": "medium",
      "detector": "review",
      "file": ".",
      "summary": "Invalid legacy login-method values are silently converted to null instead of treated as errors.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "error_consistency",
        "related_files": [
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/model/AuthFlow.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/UserService.java",
          "backend/src/main/java/com/demo/sso/service/NormalizedIdentity.java"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`AuthFlow.fromLoginMethod` returns null for blank input and also catches `IllegalArgumentException` for invalid values, returning null again.",
          "`UserService.findOrCreateUser(String...)` passes that result into `NormalizedIdentity.google(...)`, and `applyProviderIdentityFields` simply skips `lastLoginFlow` / `loginMethod` when the flow is null, so malformed legacy input is accepted without any signal while the rest of the auth pipeline uses exceptions for invalid identity data."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Make `AuthFlow.fromLoginMethod` reject unrecognized nonblank values with `IllegalArgumentException` (or return `Optional<AuthFlow>` and force `UserService` to handle invalidity explicitly) so bad legacy login-method values do not disappear silently.",
        "reasoning": "",
        "summary_hash": "2504743b"
      },
      "status": "open",
      "kind": "issue",
